const summaries = { lastRace: "Nora topped the Japan round with 47 points — Oscar Piastri finally came alive with 43 of those after two brutal races, swinging nearly 25 points above the 22.27 league average. At the other end, Mary Beth and David scraped just 2 and 3 points respectively, with Lance Stroll's mounting penalty spiral and Albon's DNF dragging both teams well into the cellar. Kimi Antonelli was the standout individual performer with 50 points, keeping Timo's lead firmly intact.", season: "Timo leads the league with 190 points, 37 ahead of Margaret in second — Kimi Antonelli's absurd 150-point season haul is the backbone of that advantage, headlined by the season's single best team score of 102 in China. Margaret is a steady second at 153 with George Russell quietly putting up elite numbers, while Charlie sits dead last at just 6 points total, Fernando Alonso's repeated DNF penalties making every race feel pointless.", players: { "Alyssa": "Sitting fourth at 105 points, your team is being carried by Max Verstappen's 77-point haul — but his back-to-back DNF penalties in China and Japan have cost you dearly and your race scores are sliding: 54, 34, 17. Sergio Perez chips in at 28 but isn't moving the needle enough to reverse that downward trend.", "Nora": "You're sixth overall at 50 points, and the season has been a wild ride — a -8 disaster in Australia nearly buried you before a 47-point Japan return sparked by Piastri's best race yet. Franco Colapinto has been the steady hand at 28 season points, but everything hinges on whether Piastri can finally stay on the road.", "Jay": "Lando Norris is doing genuine work at 35 season points, but Valtteri Bottas is a dead weight at -11 — DNF penalties in all three races have torched your potential and left you ninth at just 24 total points. Until Bottas finishes a race cleanly, your ceiling stays painfully low.", "Margaret": "You're second overall at 153 points and the most consistent team in the league — George Russell has been outstanding at 111 points with zero DNF hits, and Esteban Ocon has been a reliable 42-point sidekick. Your race scores of 48, 69, and 36 have beaten or matched the league average every single round.", "Cecelia": "Third place at 113 points with the smoothest ride in the league — scores of 42, 37, and 34 show remarkable race-to-race consistency, almost entirely on the back of Charles Leclerc's 111-point season. Gabriel Bortoleto has contributed almost nothing at just 2 total points with DNF penalties biting him twice, but Leclerc is carrying both seats.", "Timo": "You're the runaway leader at 190 points and it isn't close — Kimi Antonelli is the best-performing driver in the entire league at 150 points, delivering qualifying bonuses, fastest laps, and DotD awards on top of race points. Oliver Bearman is a useful 40-point support act, though a JPN DNF is a reminder that your second driver isn't bulletproof.", "Mary Beth": "Sitting ninth at 38 points, Lewis Hamilton is genuinely delivering at 92 points for the season, but Lance Stroll's DNF penalty tally has compounded from -25 to -45 to -65 race by race and he's dragging you to -54 on his own. Hamilton can't outrun that math — Stroll is the most damaging individual driver in the league.", "Jane": "Fifth place at 66 points, with Liam Lawson doing the real work at 50 points — his China performance was the highlight. Isack Hadjar sits at just 16 points with DNF penalties keeping him in check, and your season score is heavily inflated by one big China round; more consistency is needed from both drivers.", "David": "Eighth overall at 41 points, Carlos Sainz is pulling his weight at 41 season points but Alexander Albon has netted exactly zero after DNF penalties in China and Japan erased his race finishes. Your team scores are trending in the wrong direction — 17, 21, 3 — and a clean race from Albon is overdue.", "Charlie": "Last place at just 6 total points, and Fernando Alonso is the reason — his -17 season total comes from accumulated DNF penalties that have grown every race, and Arvid Lindblad's solid-enough 23 points simply cannot compensate. Until Alonso sees a chequered flag, this team is going nowhere.", "Sarah": "Seventh at 42 points with a quietly encouraging trajectory — after a -9 shocker in Australia when Hulkenberg's DNF sank you, you've posted 27 and 24 in the last two rounds. Pierre Gasly is the anchor at 45 season points and Hulkenberg is trending cleaner; if that holds, there's a real run at the middle of the table." } };
